('recursion', 'Recursion', 'High-throughput biology platform using AI to map cellular biology at scale for drug discovery',
 E'Recursion Pharmaceuticals operates at the intersection of robotics, machine learning, and biology - running one of the world''s largest biological datasets generated through automated, high-throughput cellular imaging experiments. The Recursion OS maps how millions of genetic and chemical perturbations affect cell morphology, creating what the company calls a "map of biology" that can predict therapeutic relevance without running traditional target-based drug discovery experiments.\n\nThe scale of the operation is the differentiator: Recursion generates petabytes of cellular imaging data weekly from its automated laboratory infrastructure, feeding a foundation model called RecursionOS that learns the language of cellular biology from experimental observations rather than from literature alone. When a new drug candidate or genetic target is queried against the model, RecursionOS can predict disease relevance, toxicity signals, and potential indications from cellular phenotype patterns - dramatically compressing the time from hypothesis to experimental validation.\n\nRecursion has clinical programs in rare genetic diseases, oncology, and infectious diseases, and has entered commercial partnerships with Roche, Bayer, and NVIDIA to extend the platform''s reach. The NVIDIA partnership specifically involves training large-scale biology foundation models on Recursion''s dataset combined with NVIDIA''s computational infrastructure - positioning Recursion as a platform company for AI biology rather than a pure drug discovery shop. For researchers and pharma companies interested in phenotypic drug discovery augmented by AI at a scale that is impossible to replicate in-house, Recursion offers both collaboration partnerships and technology licensing.',
 'https://recursion.com', 'https://recursion.com',
 'paid', false, NULL, 4.5, 420, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['biotech', 'drug-discovery', 'ai-research'],
 ARRAY['Largest AI-biology dataset from automated high-throughput cellular imaging at petabyte scale', 'RecursionOS foundation model trained on experimental biology - not just published literature', 'Active clinical programs in rare diseases and oncology validate the discovery platform in practice', 'Commercial partnerships with Roche, Bayer, and NVIDIA provide external validation and scale'],
 ARRAY['Platform access requires partnership or licensing agreement - not a standalone tool for small teams', 'Phenotypic approach is most powerful for cellular mechanism discovery - less directly applicable to target-based programs', 'Data generation infrastructure is proprietary and cannot be replicated without significant capital investment', 'Clinical translation timelines are still measured in years despite AI acceleration of early stages'],
 ARRAY['Phenotypic drug discovery for rare genetic diseases with unknown or poorly validated targets', 'Toxicity prediction and safety profiling using cellular phenotype patterns from experimental data', 'Indication expansion by querying existing compounds against the RecursionOS cellular biology map'],
