('deep-genomics', 'Deep Genomics', 'AI platform for RNA-based therapeutic discovery targeting genetic diseases',
 E'Deep Genomics applies deep learning to the problem of understanding how genetic variants cause disease and how RNA-targeting therapeutics can correct them. The company''s Big Discovery Platform analyzes the genome to predict how mutations affect RNA splicing, expression, and protein function - translating the biological consequences of genetic variants into therapeutic hypotheses for RNA-based medicines including antisense oligonucleotides (ASOs), siRNA, and splice-switching therapies.\n\nThe platform''s core capability is variant effect prediction at scale: given a genetic variant identified in a patient population, Deep Genomics'' AI predicts whether the variant affects RNA processing, what the downstream protein consequences are, and whether an RNA therapeutic strategy could correct the pathological mechanism. This is particularly valuable for rare genetic diseases where the variant biology is incompletely understood and traditional experimental characterization of every patient variant is impractical.\n\nDeep Genomics has advanced ASO programs into clinical development for rare neurological diseases including Wilson disease and Huntington disease, using the platform to design therapeutic sequences predicted to restore normal RNA splicing in patients with specific causative variants. The company operates as both an internal drug discovery pipeline and a platform licensing partner for pharmaceutical companies with RNA therapeutic programs. For researchers working on rare genetic diseases or RNA medicine, Deep Genomics represents the most sophisticated application of AI to genetic variant interpretation and RNA therapeutic design currently in clinical development.',
 'https://deepgenomics.com', 'https://deepgenomics.com',
 'paid', false, NULL, 4.4, 180, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['biotech', 'drug-discovery', 'genomics'],
 ARRAY['Variant effect prediction translates genetic mutations into RNA therapeutic hypotheses at scale', 'Clinical programs in Wilson disease and Huntington disease validate the platform in rare CNS indications', 'Platform covers ASO, siRNA, and splice-switching modalities - addressing multiple RNA therapeutic formats', 'Rare disease focus aligns with high unmet need and regulatory incentives for orphan drug development'],
 ARRAY['Highly specialized platform for RNA-based therapeutics - not applicable to small-molecule programs', 'Clinical validation is still in progress - Phase I/II data for key programs expected 2025-2027', 'Platform access for external partners requires partnership agreements with negotiated terms', 'Rare disease target validation requires patient genetic data that may be difficult to access early in programs'],
 ARRAY['RNA therapeutic sequence design for rare genetic diseases caused by splicing or expression defects', 'Patient stratification by variant effect prediction to identify the patient subpopulations most likely to respond', 'Mechanism-of-action characterization for genetic variants of unknown significance in disease cohorts'],
