('exscientia', 'Exscientia', 'AI-first drug design platform for automated small-molecule candidate generation and optimization',
 E'Exscientia is an AI-driven drug design company that uses automated design-make-test-analyse cycles to compress the time from project initiation to clinical candidate to a fraction of the traditional timeline. The company''s Centaur Chemist platform combines generative AI for molecular design with automated synthesis and high-throughput screening to run iterative optimization cycles that would take a traditional medicinal chemistry team months in weeks instead.\n\nThe clinical track record is the most compelling evidence for the platform: Exscientia has advanced multiple AI-designed drug candidates into Phase I clinical trials including DSP-1181 (developed with Sumitomo Dainippon for OCD) - the first AI-designed drug candidate to enter human trials - and multiple oncology and immunology programs. The speed advantage is validated in comparative terms: Exscientia has repeatedly demonstrated initial hit-to-candidate timelines under 12 months for programs that typically require 3 to 4 years by traditional methods.\n\nFor pharmaceutical partners, Exscientia offers collaboration models where the platform is applied to partner targets, with Exscientia retaining co-development rights. The company has partnerships with Sanofi, Bristol Myers Squibb, and Evotec among others. The AI platform is not a standalone licensed software product - Exscientia operates as a drug discovery service and co-development partner rather than selling platform access. For pharma companies and investors evaluating AI drug discovery partnerships, Exscientia''s clinical proof-of-concept portfolio represents the strongest validation of AI-accelerated medicinal chemistry currently available.',
 'https://exscientia.ai', 'https://exscientia.ai',
