('generate-biomedicines', 'Generate Biomedicines', 'Generative AI platform for designing protein therapeutics from first principles',
 E'Generate Biomedicines applies generative AI to the design of protein-based therapeutics - antibodies, enzymes, and other biological molecules that represent the fastest-growing class of approved drugs. The company''s Chroma platform uses diffusion models for protein structure generation, enabling the design of novel protein sequences with specified structural and functional properties from scratch rather than through iterative modification of natural protein scaffolds.\n\nThe fundamental capability that Chroma enables is programmable biology: specifying the desired properties of a therapeutic protein - binding target, selectivity, stability, half-life - and generating novel protein sequences that satisfy those constraints computationally, before any laboratory synthesis or testing. For biologics drug discovery, where the traditional approach involves generating and screening millions of antibody variants in animal or cell-based systems, generative protein design compresses the discovery phase dramatically by intelligently navigating the vast protein sequence space using AI priors about what protein structures are physically realizable and functionally stable.\n\nGenerate Biomedicines has raised significant capital and assembled a team that combines deep learning researchers from leading AI institutions with drug discovery scientists from major pharmaceutical companies. The company runs its own internal pipeline of AI-designed therapeutic proteins across oncology and immunology indications. For pharmaceutical companies evaluating biologic drug discovery partnerships that move beyond traditional antibody screening toward truly AI-native protein design, Generate Biomedicines represents one of the leading examples of generative protein AI applied to clinical-grade therapeutics. Platform access is through research collaboration and partnership agreements.',
 'https://generatebiomedicines.com', 'https://generatebiomedicines.com',
 'paid', false, NULL, 4.4, 160, false, false, false,
